you have a workspace for dev QA product. so unfortunately, you've deleted the prod workspace, so what will happen now?

What happens when you delete prod workspace:

terraform workspace delete prod
        │
        ▼
State file for prod → DELETED permanently
Resources in AWS    → STILL RUNNING ✅
Terraform control   → LOST ❌

Immediate impact:

Prod resources still running in AWS
But Terraform has no state file
If someone runs terraform apply → 
creates DUPLICATE resources ❌
If someone runs terraform destroy →
won't find anything in state ❌
Complete drift between Terraform and AWS

Option 1 — State file in S3 backend (best case):

# If you configured remote backend like this:
terraform {
  backend "s3" {
    bucket = "my-terraform-state"
    key    = "prod/terraform.tfstate"
    region = "us-east-2"
  }
}

# State file still in S3 even if workspace deleted
# Go to S3 bucket → find prod state file
# Recreate workspace and restore

# Step 1 - recreate prod workspace
terraform workspace new prod

# Step 2 - state already in S3
# just switch to prod
terraform workspace select prod

# Step 3 - verify
terraform state list
terraform plan    # should show no changes ✅
---------
Option 2 — Local backend (worst case):

State file stored locally
workspace delete → state file gone forever
No recovery possible ❌

Only option:
→ terraform import every resource manually
→ one by one bring back into state

Recovery steps for local backend:

# Step 1 - recreate prod workspace
terraform workspace new prod

# Step 2 - import all resources one by one
terraform import aws_instance.web      i-1111111
terraform import aws_instance.app      i-2222222
terraform import aws_db_instance.prod  my-prod-db
terraform import aws_vpc.prod          vpc-12345

# Step 3 - verify
terraform plan    # should show no changes
